<package>
	<metadata>
		<id>Cqrs.Modelling</id>
		<title>UML modelling tools for CQRS.NET</title>
		<version>$version$</version>
		<authors>Chinchilla Software</authors>
		<licenseUrl>http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0</licenseUrl>
		<projectUrl>https://getcqrs.net</projectUrl>
		<iconUrl>https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Chinchilla-Software-Com/CQRS/master/wiki/ChinChilla-Software-Red.png</iconUrl>
		<requireLicenseAcceptance>false</requireLicenseAcceptance>
		<description>Uml templates and a Visual Studio VISX profile package for the lightweight CQRS framework. Using this package you can generate much of the boiler plate code involved in implementing a CQRS project.</description>
		<summary>
			Uml profiles for the lightweight CQRS.net framework. Using this package you can generate much of the boiler plate code involved in implementing a scalable, enterprise grade CQRS project ready for deployent on-premise or on Azure.

			Model commands, events and aggregates visually and let all the handlers and boiler plate code be generated for you utilising the CQRS.net platform.
		</summary>
		<copyright>Copyright 2013</copyright>
		<tags>CQRS UML Modelling</tags>

		<releaseNotes>
			Version 1.601

			* Added code generation for the base Host class.
			* Added new stereo type on relationships to visually model aggregate to event EventHandlers
			* Added new stereo type on relationships to visually model event to command converter EventHandlers
			* Added new stereo type on relationships to visually model command to aggregate CommandHandlers
			* Updated the EventHandlerTemplate.t4 to properly target any event and an entity optionally. If no Entity is specified the generated class name is that of the model class.
		</releaseNotes>
	</metadata>
	<files>
		<file src="bin\Release\*.vsix" target="VisualStudioAddOns" />
		<file src="..\Templates\*.t4" target="Templates" />
		<file src="..\Templates\Basic\*.t4" target="Templates\Basic" />
		<file src="*.ps1" target="Tools" />
	</files>
</package>